WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.930 --> 00:00:13.970
The asphalt burns 
and sweat oozes out of every pore

2
00:00:14.300 --> 00:00:16.930
as the blazing sun saps your energy away.

3
00:00:16.930 --> 00:00:19.230
I get it. I feel your pain.

4
00:00:19.540 --> 00:00:21.610
I'm in sales, too, after all.

5
00:00:21.610 --> 00:00:23.330
But I must apologize.

6
00:00:23.330 --> 00:00:27.930
My words of empathy, spoken in the 
chilly confines of this smoking room,

7
00:00:27.930 --> 00:00:31.440
hold no water at all, and I know that.

8
00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:39.410
This little act isn't helping.

9
00:00:42.330 --> 00:00:46.090
Why is the damn A/C out of order?!

10
00:00:46.090 --> 00:00:48.010
This must be part 
of the chief's master plan!

11
00:00:48.010 --> 00:00:51.400
He probably jammed 
one of his things inside the A/C!

12
00:00:51.400 --> 00:00:54.450
He can't be that bored.

13
00:00:54.450 --> 00:00:57.800
Don't get so heated. 
You'll only feel the heat.

14
00:00:57.800 --> 00:00:59.680
Oh, fine.

15
00:01:00.040 --> 00:01:01.780
It'll get fixed tomorrow.

16
00:01:01.780 --> 00:01:03.240
It'll get fixed next week.

17
00:01:03.240 --> 00:01:05.190
It'll stay like this all summer.

18
00:01:07.130 --> 00:01:07.940
Oh?

19
00:01:08.290 --> 00:01:11.320
Good news, Suzuki. 
It'll get fixed tomorrow.

20
00:01:11.320 --> 00:01:13.410
What? How would you know that?

21
00:01:13.410 --> 00:01:17.450
My little superstition. 
It's pretty accurate, you know?

22
00:01:19.550 --> 00:01:21.820
Squee! I'm tickled pink to hear that!

23
00:01:22.210 --> 00:01:25.080
If it's not fixed tomorrow, 
you're a dead man!

24
00:01:25.080 --> 00:01:26.290
Now, now.

25
00:01:26.630 --> 00:01:29.100
Just believe in me and wait, Suzuki-san.

26
00:01:29.100 --> 00:01:31.880
A cool future is nearly upon us.

27
00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:34.320
Urk.

28
00:01:35.180 --> 00:01:37.290
G-Good evening.

29
00:01:40.460 --> 00:01:41.600
My bad.

30
00:01:41.600 --> 00:01:44.010
I was washing away some milk 
a driver spilled everywhere

31
00:01:44.010 --> 00:01:45.520
and started enjoying it too much.

32
00:01:47.200 --> 00:01:49.640
A hose is a mighty tempting plaything.

33
00:03:31.680 --> 00:03:34.260
This is weirdly tense.

34
00:03:34.930 --> 00:03:37.860
Thank you for lending me 
the towel and trousers.

35
00:03:38.300 --> 00:03:40.530
It's the least I could do, 
since it was my fault.

36
00:03:40.530 --> 00:03:42.010
Oh, not at all.

37
00:03:44.610 --> 00:03:47.750
No need to be so formal, Sasaki-kun.

38
00:03:48.220 --> 00:03:50.100
We're pretty close in age.

39
00:03:51.590 --> 00:03:53.150
W-We are?!

40
00:03:53.500 --> 00:03:56.400
You look like you're in your forties.

41
00:03:56.400 --> 00:03:59.530
And I'm forty exactly. 
Let's keep it casual.

42
00:03:59.890 --> 00:04:04.360
Someone around my age is heading the 
busiest supermarket around these parts?

43
00:04:04.360 --> 00:04:06.010
You have my utmost respect.

44
00:04:06.010 --> 00:04:09.040
Why'd that make you up the formality?

45
00:04:09.440 --> 00:04:13.300
You must be impressed every time 
you learn a person's age.

46
00:04:17.330 --> 00:04:20.800
I can only imagine how you reacted 
when you learned Tayama's.

47
00:04:20.800 --> 00:04:23.550
Huh? Tayama-san's age?

48
00:04:27.710 --> 00:04:28.810
Yeah.

49
00:04:29.530 --> 00:04:31.540
I have no idea.

50
00:04:33.110 --> 00:04:35.590
Don't you smoke together all the time?

51
00:04:35.590 --> 00:04:37.190
Y-Yeah.

52
00:04:37.560 --> 00:04:40.110
You don't ask her any personal questions?

53
00:04:40.110 --> 00:04:41.220
I don't.

54
00:04:41.220 --> 00:04:43.770
Do you just have no interest in people?

55
00:04:43.770 --> 00:04:44.580
Huh?

56
00:04:46.090 --> 00:04:48.480
Of course I'm interested.

57
00:04:53.090 --> 00:04:55.460
While she messes with me at times,

58
00:04:55.890 --> 00:04:59.090
she still talks to an old dude like me.

59
00:04:59.740 --> 00:05:03.180
How could I not want 
to get to know her better?

60
00:05:05.350 --> 00:05:10.170
But I enjoy just listening to the things 
she wants to talk about.

61
00:05:19.850 --> 00:05:24.700
The rest I can just wonder 
about as I walk home.

62
00:05:26.080 --> 00:05:28.460
No wonder she took to him.

63
00:05:29.990 --> 00:05:31.330
I get it now.

64
00:05:32.010 --> 00:05:34.920
So you're saying you do like Tayama-san?

65
00:05:34.920 --> 00:05:37.240
Whoa! Can we not jump to conclusions?!

66
00:05:37.240 --> 00:05:38.130
Do you hate her, then?

67
00:05:38.390 --> 00:05:40.010
You know I don't!

68
00:05:40.370 --> 00:05:42.200
Then what exactly is it?

69
00:05:42.200 --> 00:05:44.140
I mean, of course I lik...

70
00:05:44.140 --> 00:05:46.370
Heya, I dropped by after a shopping trip.

71
00:05:54.620 --> 00:05:55.460
Hmm?

72
00:05:57.060 --> 00:05:57.840
Tch.

73
00:05:59.150 --> 00:06:03.190
I'm sorry, Sasaki-kun. I've been summoned 
to deal with a customer complaint.

74
00:06:04.290 --> 00:06:06.620
I'll be back with money 
to pay for your dry cleaning.

75
00:06:06.620 --> 00:06:08.280
Have a chat with Tayama in the meantime.

76
00:06:08.280 --> 00:06:10.790
Oh, okay...

77
00:06:10.790 --> 00:06:12.350
Bye.

78
00:06:18.090 --> 00:06:20.550
You're soaked, Sasaki-san.

79
00:06:20.550 --> 00:06:24.430
Oh, yeah, I had a little accident.

80
00:06:24.770 --> 00:06:25.970
Huh...

81
00:06:36.850 --> 00:06:39.280
By the way, uh, Tayama-san?

82
00:06:39.280 --> 00:06:41.190
Did you hear all that?

83
00:06:41.990 --> 00:06:43.440
Hear all what?

84
00:06:45.050 --> 00:06:48.040
Nothing. It was no big deal.

85
00:06:48.040 --> 00:06:50.950
Your manager and I 
were just making small talk—

86
00:06:52.930 --> 00:06:54.970
Wait, what? T-Tayama-san?

87
00:06:54.970 --> 00:06:57.460
You need to dry your hair.

88
00:06:57.460 --> 00:07:00.210
Uh, I didn't get my head wet...

89
00:07:01.720 --> 00:07:03.140
Twenty-four.

90
00:07:07.630 --> 00:07:08.470
Wh...

91
00:07:09.010 --> 00:07:11.450
What is that number?

92
00:07:12.890 --> 00:07:17.980
You can wonder about that 
as you walk home.
